This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques for word sense induction and disambiguation, which are typically studied in the subfield of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also uses word embeddings, which are a popular tool in machine learning and deep learning research (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves clustering and classification tasks, which are common in information retrieval (cs.IR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. Finally, the paper uses neural machine translation systems, which are a type of neural network architecture commonly used in natural language processing and related fields (cs.NE).
